3","updated":"2026-06-13","tags":["#laboratorio-medico","#source","#sipmel","#interferenze-analitiche","#fase-preanalitica"],"status":"developing","address":"c-000091","source_type":"guideline","author":"Margherita Morandini (GdS VEA SIPMeL)","publication":"Riv Ital Med Lab 2022;18:42-56, DOI: 10.23736/S1825-859X.22.00135-9","related":["[[SIPMeL]]","[[Gruppo di Studio Variabilità Extra-Analitica (GdS VEA) SIPMeL]]","[[Interferenze Endogene HIL (Emolisi, Ittero, Lipemia)]]","[[Falsi Positivi e Falsi Negativi in Diagnostica di Laboratorio]]","[[Fase Preanalitica]]","[[ISO 15189]]"],"key_claims":["L'ittero (iperbilirubinemia, cute/sclere/mucose giallastre per bilirubina >1.5-2.5 mg/dL) causa interferenza analitica di tipo fisico (assorbimento luce 400-520 nm, picco 456 nm) o chimico (interferenza con reagenti di metodi chimici/enzimatici, es. H2O2 nella reazione Trinder).","L'interferenza negativa è più frequente per creatinina (metodo Jaffe), proteine totali, colesterolo totale e HDL, ammoniaca, folato e tobramicina; un'interferenza positiva può coinvolgere fosforo, magnesio, urea, FT3, testosterone, estradiolo, fruttosamina, acetaminofene, fenobarbitale, teofillina.","La frequenza dell'interferenza da ittero (I-index oltre soglia 10) è 0.14% su 414.502 campioni, con incidenza variabile per singolo test: 0.06% creatinina, 2.2% proteine totali, 3.9% ammoniaca - meno frequente dell'emolisi ma più frequente della lipemia.","I risultati su test specifici sono spesso discordanti tra strumenti/produttori (Roche Cobas, Siemens Vista, Abbott Alinity), evidenziando la mancanza di armonizzazione degli indici HIL tra sistemi analitici.","Il dibattito sull'interferenza da ittero sui test coagulativi foto-ottici (PT, aPTT, D-dimero) resta non risolto, con studi contraddittori; a I-index 50 alcuni studi riportano falsi allungamenti di PT (10%) e aPTT (12%).","Nel liquido cefalo-rachidiano, un'iperbilirubinemia >20 umol/L (1.17 mg/dL) può causare falsa positività per emorragia subaracnoidea (xantocromia).","Nelle urine, bilirubinuria e urobilinogeno rilevati da dipstick possono segnalare falsi positivi di chetoni, esterasi leucocitaria e glucosio, e falsi negativi di pH e nitriti, oltre a interferire sulla creatininuria.","Per la refertazione dei test plasmatici interferiti si raccomanda: diluire se esiste metodo di diluizione convalidato; cancellare il risultato se non c'è metodo di diluizione validato o se l'LoQ diluito è clinicamente critico; aggiungere un commento standardizzato se il produttore attesta assenza di interferenza fino alla concentrazione testata."]},"task_lines":[],"tasks":{},"codeblock_ranges":[]},"smart_blocks:Wiki/sources/SIPMeL - Interferenza da Ittero.md#---frontmatter---": {"path":null,"last_embed":{"hash":"1cnbkq6","at":1781675970583},"embeddings":{"TaylorAI/bge-micro-v2":{"vec":[-0.03666741,-0.01741193,0.01031715,-0.00056282,0.00498672,-0.10053869,0.03566161,0.04681638,-0.00967401,0.02540162,0.01706512,-0.0690173,0.00759468,0.0203542,0.01309142,-0.0060453,0.01464414,-0.00009055,-0.03061188,-0.0239807,0.12065937,-0.01292774,-0.0282921,-0.04308574,0.03686429,0.0525169,0.00463238,-0.02911593,-0.05411874,-0.22479297,0.03065819,0.04875502,-0.00946623,-0.01488025,-0.02312985,0.03256285,-0.01233151,0.04329639,0.01286341,0.02935255,0.04155874,0.06206017,-0.04089205,-0.03282309,-0.03912025,-0.04244218,-0.02333862,0.05442288,-0.00566502,-0.03003392,-0.06725888,-0.00485369,0.02721044,0.05463678,0.00702119,0.06303026,0.04801365,0.0167107,0.03186063,0.04255898,0.11503937,0.04922047,-0.24248444,0.08899699,0.0176016,0.03403567,-0.05628386,-0.0006104,-0.00893187,0.01357434,-0.04329769,-0.04179658,-0.0125013,0.01097869,0.01861737,-0.01119375,0.00113376,0.00283826,0.02049644,-0.00574658,-0.00460933,0.03246476,0.00690441,0.00717942,0.0075225,-0.02523236,0.04254488,0.01083242,0.02750465,-0.02092643,-0.03253026,-0.0497134,0.07386289,0.03777814,-0.00567064,0.03493184,-0.02084712,0.00525114,-0.03825953,0.07869262,-0.03986538,-0.01907039,-0.